cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 65 miles WSW of St. Petersburg, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: Turning north-northeast then northeast, crossing northern Florida and moving offshore the southeast U.S. coast toward the western Atlantic
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: northern Florida peninsula (near the Big Bend coast south of Cedar Key)

weather_observation.watch_coast: N/A – watches confined to Florida coast only
weather_observation.warning_coast: N/A – warnings confined to Florida coast only
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Florida Gulf Coast tonight and Thursday; then parts of coastal Georgia and the Carolinas as the system emerges into the Atlantic
weather_observation.wind: Only a slight (≤3%) chance of tropical-storm-force gusts; prevailing winds likely below gale force
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected for Virginia – surge warnings limited to Florida Gulf Coast
weather_observation.rainfall: Light to moderate rain bands possible Friday as the remnant depression passes well offshore
weather_observation.other_hazards: Rip currents and rough surf possible along the Virginia capes late Friday into Saturday
